    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>It thrills me just a little everytime I come across a pot de creme recipe&#8211;Dorie Greenspan had one with cardamom and coffee not long ago, yum&#8211;after a sorry experience late last year at a nicer restaurant when I asked if the &#8220;chocolate selection&#8221; dessert included a pot de creme. The server had no idea, and retreated to the kitchen. He came back and said, &#8220;no, and they&#8217;ve never even heard of that.&#8221; I begged to differ&#8211;pots de creme clearly exist. Server chappy said &#8220;yes, well, the chef is FRENCH, you know.&#8221; It seemed I was meant to infer that he was thus in all ways superior to me, the server, and pretty much everyone else in the room. So I left an otherwise delightful dinner thinking, &#8220;well then how the hell did he get this far without even HEARING of pots de creme???&#8221;</></>So thanks for once again reinforcing the existence of a truly stellar dessert.</p>
    </div>

